## 2. Restrictions

The Licensee shall **not**:

- resell, sublicense, rent, lease, or otherwise **redistribute the source code** (or a substantial part of it) to any third party in source form;
- distribute the unmodified Software as a competing source‑code product or SDK;
- remove or alter the license header, copyright notices, or the build watermark (if any).

**For clarity:** the OEM grant in §1 permits shipping the Software **embedded in** the Licensee's own product (compiled/binary). It does **not** permit redistributing the Software **as** a source SDK, library, or developer tool on its own, or as a "naked" repackaging of this SDK – that protects the Licensor as the original producer rather than breeding resellers.

Distributing **compiled binaries** of the Licensee's own application that incorporate the Software (modified or not) is permitted. Distributing the **source code** of the Software on its own is **not** permitted.

